title: 880-02 Sharḥ al-Sullam : manuscript / ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn Muḥammad al-Akhḍarī.
880-02 Sharḥ al-Sullam : manuscript / ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn Muḥammad al-Akhḍarī.
Book of accounts, 1793-1803.
note_text: Caption title; the 22 p. at end contain the doctor's handwritten comments on some patients tended during 1793-95.

title: Excelsior diary : Columbian edition, 1893 / [signed in ink on title page: Geo. W. Vansint].
note_text: Although this is obviously a physician's book, detailing his practice in New York City, I can find no listing of Vansint in Polk's, AMA, NUC, New York Acad., or Worldcat directories.

title: Ballad on Mrs. Strawbridge : manuscript.
note_text: Title and attribution to George Bubb Doddington from Horace Walpole's autograph copy of the same verses. See: Yale edition of Horace Walpole's correspondence, v. 34, pages 262-263.

title: Inventaire du Trésor des chartes : manuscript.
note_text: Title from caption on the first page of text in volume I: "Commission pour travailler a l'inventaire du tresor des chartes".

title: Lectures delivered by John Lindley in the junior course of botany at University College London.
note_text: Devised title and date based on the manuscript's dedication title page: "To my daughter Mary Elizabeth, these notes of the lectures delivered in the junior course of botany by Dr. Lindley at University College London, are inscribed by her affectionate father, 1848."

title: Collection of Medical remedies.
note_text: The approximate date is taken from folio 174v: "The kings medicen for the plague used in london anno div. 1545."

title: Under the earth lies the skin ..., not after 1806.
note_text: Attributed to René de Percy based on manuscript note in a different hand below poem: By [the] Abbé́ Percy échantillon of English.

title: Letter offering employment as a draughtsman or clerk, not after 1806?
note_text: Date based on death date of Richard Bull, who owned and likely assembled the album in which this letter was found.

title: Charter granted by Edward VI to the burgesses of Devizes.
note_text: Date from end of document: the xxvii daye of Novembre in [th]e fyrste yeare of ow[r] kynge.
